│[1m [0m[1mpatch_description       [0m[1m [0m│ Introduce a lightweight physics-inspired relaxation step to spread circles more           │
│[1m                          [0m│ efficiently before the local search. This helps avoid cramped initial configurations and  │
│[1m                          [0m│ allows larger radii to emerge from the compute_max_radii step. The improvement comprises: │
│[1m                          [0m│ - A new relax_layout that gently repels overlapping circles and nudges them away from     │
│[1m                          [0m│ walls.                                                                                    │
│[1m                          [0m│ - A call to relax_layout immediately after the initial placement, prior to the simulated  │
│[1m                          [0m│ annealing local search.                                                                   │
│[1m                          [0m│ - A more aggressive local search (larger initial step and more iterations) to leverage    │
│[1m                          [0m│ the better starting arrangement.                                                          │
│[1m                          [0m│                                                                                           │
│[1m                          [0m│ Overall, this should yield larger total radii and move towards the better-known           │
│[1m                          [0m│ benchmarks (closer to 2.6+).                                                              │
